<subSubSection id="C30175E2FFBCFFAFC6F45601FAEDF819" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA42669FFBCFFAFC6F45601FAEDF819" blockId="8.[151,1437,798,1977]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC6F45601FEB9F8EC" bold="true" box="[199,308,1842,1868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFBCFFAFC4B05600FB19F8EC" authority="Disney et Michailovskaya, 2000" authorityName="Disney et Michailovskaya" authorityYear="2000" box="[643,1172,1842,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setipalpatus">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC4B05600FCA9F8EC" box="[643,804,1842,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">P. setipalpatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFBCFFAFC5195601FB19F8EC" author="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V." box="[810,1172,1842,1868]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="35 - 45" refId="ref22089" refString="Disney, R. H. L. &amp; Michailovskaya, M. V. (2000) New species of Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera: Phoridae) from the Far East of Russia. Fragmenta Faunistica, 43 (4), 35 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.3161 / 00159301 FF 2000.43.4.035" type="journal article" year="2000">
Disney 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC54C5600FC1EF8EC" box="[895,915,1843,1868]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">et</emphasis>
Michailovskaya, 2000
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it is distinguished from the latter by apical seta shorter than maximum width of palpus, and abdominal sternite VI with 4–5 inclinate, long setae each side. This species looks also similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1B5DEAFFBCFFAFC4E35648FBEAF834" authority="Zhang et Liu, 2019" authorityName="Zhang et Liu" authorityYear="2019" box="[720,1127,1914,1940]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Pseudacteon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trapeziformis">
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC4E35648FC0CF834" box="[720,897,1914,1940]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">P. trapeziformis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF8A5B98FFBCFFAFC5B95649FBEAF834" author="Zhang, J. &amp; Liu, G. C." box="[906,1127,1914,1940]" pageId="8" pageNumber="209" pagination="448 - 450" refId="ref22531" refString="Zhang, J. &amp; Liu, G. C. (2019) A new species of the ant-parasitizing genus Pseudacteon Coquillett (Diptera, Phoridae) from China. Zootaxa, 4629 (3), 448 - 450. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4629.3.12" type="journal article" year="2019">
Zhang 
<emphasis id="B96FFA7BFFBCFFAFC5E95648FC63F834" box="[986,1006,1915,1940]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="209">et</emphasis>
Liu, 2019
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, it differs from the latter in having more frontal setulae, longer setae of palpus and the number and arrangement of setulae on sternite VI.
</paragraph>
